---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="CHA &mdash; AI SRE one-pager"
  description="One-page rationale + architecture for CHA — the in-cluster, policy-bounded, audit-anchored autonomous SRE for Kubernetes. Bring-your-own-LLM. Open core. Slack-able."
>
  <style is:global>
    @media print {
      header[role='banner'], header, nav, footer { display: none !important; }
      main { padding: 0 !important; }
      .onepager { padding: 0.5in !important; }
      .onepager-grid { gap: 0.35in !important; }
      a { color: inherit !important; text-decoration: none !important; }
      .no-print { display: none !important; }
      body { background: #fff !important; }
    }
    @page { size: Letter portrait; margin: 0.4in; }
  </style>

  <section class="onepager mx-auto max-w-5xl px-6 py-12 text-zinc-900 dark:text-zinc-100">
    <div class="no-print mb-6 flex items-center justify-between text-sm">
      <a
        href="/"
        class="font-medium text-accent-600 hover:text-accent-700 dark:text-accent-400 dark:hover:text-accent-300"
      >
        &larr; Back to home
      </a>
      <button
        type="button"
        onclick="window.print()"
        class="rounded-md border border-zinc-300 bg-white px-3 py-1.5 text-xs font-medium text-zinc-900 shadow-sm transition hover:bg-zinc-50 dark:border-zinc-700 dark:bg-zinc-900 dark:text-zinc-100 dark:hover:bg-zinc-800"
      >
        Print &middot; Save as PDF
      </button>
    </div>

    <header class="border-b-2 border-zinc-900 pb-4 dark:border-zinc-100">
      <p class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-widest text-accent-600 dark:text-accent-400">
        CHA &middot; Cluster Health Autopilot
      </p>
      <h1 class="mt-1 text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight">
        Autonomous SRE for Kubernetes.
      </h1>
      <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-zinc-600 dark:text-zinc-400">
        In-cluster &middot; Policy-bounded &middot; Audit-anchored &middot;
        Bring-your-own-LLM &middot; Apache-2.0 open core
      </p>
    </header>

    <div class="onepager-grid mt-6 grid gap-8 md:grid-cols-2">

      <div>
        <h2 class="text-base font-semibold uppercase tracking-wider text-zinc-900 dark:text-zinc-100">
          Why agentic SRE &gt; AIOps observability
        </h2>
        <dl class="mt-3 space-y-3 text-sm leading-snug text-zinc-700 dark:text-zinc-300">
          <div>
            <dt class="font-semibold text-zinc-900 dark:text-zinc-100">
              Closed-loop is the default, not a roadmap milestone.
            </dt>
            <dd class="mt-0.5">
              Every cycle: detect &rarr; propose fix &rarr; (operator click) &rarr;
              apply &rarr; re-diagnose. Komodor, Robusta, Causely, NeuBird,
              Resolve, Ciroos: they observe and summarise. CHA mutates.
            </dd>
          </div>
          <div>
            <dt class="font-semibold text-zinc-900 dark:text-zinc-100">
              In-cluster &mdash; no telemetry exfiltration.
            </dt>
            <dd class="mt-0.5">
              No SaaS endpoint. No vendor LLM lock-in. Point at any
              OpenAI-compatible endpoint &mdash; in-cluster vLLM, Azure OpenAI,
              your own gateway. Cluster data and prompts never leave your
              perimeter. Air-gap, sovereign, k3s edge: all supported.
            </dd>
          </div>
          <div>
            <dt class="font-semibold text-zinc-900 dark:text-zinc-100">
              Eight-layer action policy &mdash; the leash on the agent.
            </dt>
            <dd class="mt-0.5">
              Action-kind allowlist, target-resource scope, namespace
              protection, GitOps-managed skip, signed JWT click-to-fix,
              dual-approval for T3 vault break-glass, hash-chained audit,
              per-(approver, class) rate budget. All in Apache-2.0 source.
            </dd>
          </div>
          <div>
            <dt class="font-semibold text-zinc-900 dark:text-zinc-100">
              Open core &mdash; you can read it before you install.
            </dt>
            <dd class="mt-0.5">
              OSS engine is Apache-2.0: 12 K8s probes + 4 M2 probes,
              30 cloud probes (AWS/GCP/Azure), 6 drift-class analyzers (v1.8),
              5 policy-bounded fixers, controller-runtime operator.
              CHA-com paid tier adds the LLM Investigator + T0&ndash;T3 AI SRE
              ladder.
            </dd>
          </div>
        </dl>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="text-base font-semibold uppercase tracking-wider text-zinc-900 dark:text-zinc-100">
          Architecture &mdash; the autopilot loop
        </h2>
        <pre class="mt-3 overflow-hidden whitespace-pre rounded-md border border-zinc-300 bg-zinc-50 p-3 font-mono text-[10px] leading-tight text-zinc-900 dark:border-zinc-700 dark:bg-zinc-950 dark:text-zinc-100">{`
   ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
   │   In-cluster watcher (leader-elected, K8s 1.27+)     │
   │                                                      │
   │   Probes ── 12 K8s ── 10 AWS ── 3 drift-class        │
   │     │        Nodes    RDS     GitOps (Argo/Flux)     │
   │     │        Pods     EBS     WorkloadState (CNPG)   │
   │     │        Postgres EKS     RBAC (wildcards/SA)    │
   │     │        Ceph     IAM                            │
   │     ▼                                                │
   │   Diagnose ──► DriftReport CRDs                      │
   │     │                                                │
   │     ▼                                                │
   │   T0 narration (LLM) ──► Slack / Alertmanager        │
   │     │                                                │
   │     ▼                                                │
   │   T1 fix proposer (LLM, JSON-mode)                   │
   │     │   ╭── patch_validator: JSONPath allow-list     │
   │     │   ╰── action_kind allowlist (closed enum)      │
   │     ▼                                                │
   │   Ed25519-signed JWT click-to-fix URL                │
   │     │   ── delivered to operator via Slack / ticket  │
   │     │   ── expiry + JTI replay protection            │
   │     ▼                                                │
   │   Operator clicks ──► Mutate (5 fixers)              │
   │     │                                                │
   │     ▼                                                │
   │   T2 multi-step planner / T3 vault runbook           │
   │   (dual-approval, 30-min window, key names only)     │
   │     │                                                │
   │     ▼                                                │
   │   Re-diagnose ──► DriftReport status: resolved       │
   │     │                                                │
   │     ▼                                                │
   │   AuditEvent (hash-chained, prev_hash)               │
   │     ── JSONL sink (operator-controlled)              │
   │     ── Prometheus metrics                            │
   └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
`}</pre>

        <h2 class="mt-4 text-base font-semibold uppercase tracking-wider text-zinc-900 dark:text-zinc-100">
          T0 &rarr; T3 tier ladder
        </h2>
        <ul class="mt-2 space-y-1 text-xs leading-snug text-zinc-700 dark:text-zinc-300">
          <li><strong class="text-zinc-900 dark:text-zinc-100">T0 Narration</strong> &mdash; LLM-enriched diagnostic text in Slack &middot; sub-second latency on in-cluster Qwen 3.6 35B</li>
          <li><strong class="text-zinc-900 dark:text-zinc-100">T1 Fix proposer</strong> &mdash; agent picks action_kind from whitelist; JWT click-to-fix URL</li>
          <li><strong class="text-zinc-900 dark:text-zinc-100">T2 Planner</strong> &mdash; multi-step plan, each step still a JWT click; plan signed as a unit</li>
          <li><strong class="text-zinc-900 dark:text-zinc-100">T3 Vault break-glass</strong> &mdash; runbook text + dual-approval timeline; CHA never executes, operator runs manually</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

    </div>

    <footer class="mt-8 border-t-2 border-zinc-900 pt-4 text-xs text-zinc-600 dark:border-zinc-100 dark:text-zinc-400">
      <div class="flex flex-wrap items-baseline justify-between gap-3">
        <div>
          <p class="font-mono">
            $ helm repo add cha https://bionic-ai-solutions.github.io/cluster-health-autopilot/
          </p>
          <p class="font-mono">$ helm install cha cha/cluster-health-autopilot</p>
        </div>
        <div class="text-right">
          <p class="font-semibold text-zinc-900 dark:text-zinc-100">
            https://asre.baisoln.com
          </p>
          <p>github.com/Bionic-AI-Solutions/cluster-health-autopilot</p>
          <p>salil.kadam@gmail.com</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <p class="mt-2 text-[10px] text-zinc-500 dark:text-zinc-500">
        v1.8.2 shipped 2026-05-28 &middot; OSS Apache-2.0 &middot; T0&ndash;T3 verified live against Qwen 3.6 35B (in-cluster vLLM)
      </p>
    </footer>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
